title: Dolphins 'obsessed' with Josh Rosen, Jarvis Landry contract extension
description:
Adam Beasley of the Miami Herald joins Will Brinson to take a look at the Dolphins plans for the draft and grade their offseason. First, the guys dive into the Jarvis Landry extension from the Browns, which featured a whopping $47 million in guaranteed money, and debate whether or not the 49ers can keep Reuben Foster around. Beasley then gives his grade on the Dolphins offseason and reveals which quarterback (it's Josh Rosen) that Adam Gase is "obsessed" with.
